The paper deals with the problem of identifying a team of skilled individuals for collaboration, in the presence of a social network. This involves measuring team compatibility in terms of collaborative compatibility, which is a social network analysis problem. Therefore, cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The problem of identifying a team that maximizes the collaborative compatibility is a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of approximation algorithms, which is a sub-field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of heuristics, which is a sub-field of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves the use of graph theory, which is a sub-field of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
